    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (80.29) and **Christian Yelich** (75.84) serving as our primary offensive catalysts. **Yordan Alvarez** sits at the top of our rankings against Emerson Hancock, benefiting from a massive 19% SP skill boost and a favorable order position in the #2 hole, which maximizes his plate appearances against a shaky rotation. **Christian Yelich** remains a high-floor play against Jake Irvin; despite a slight park penalty, his elite platoon advantage (+13%) and projected top-of-the-order usage make him a core component of today's scoring strategy. **Junior Caminero** (76.16) also presents a high-upside play, as he draws the favorable matchup against Luis Gil, who carries a shaky 5.74 xERA.\n\nSpeed remains the focus for our stolen base-heavy build, and while **Victor Scott II** and **Logan O'Hoppe** were heavily considered, both fell below the 40.0 \"Below Floor\" threshold due to unfavorable matchups against tough left-handed pitching and elite arms, respectively. **Chase Meidroth** (51.80) was our most difficult cut; despite his optimal spot at the top of the order, he ultimately sat due to a 31% rain risk and a lower projected efficiency compared to our utilized MI/UTIL slots. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Josh Smith** (52.05) and **Hyeseong Kim** (61.59); both are currently optimized in our projected lineups due to their \"slow delivery\" exploit against their respective opponents, which significantly elevates their potential to secure stolen bases despite being slotted lower in the batting order.\n\nManagement notes that lineup volatility remains a factor, as **Josh Smith**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Christian Yelich**, **Yordan Alvarez**, and **Hyeseong Kim** are all pending confirmation. While **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (66.90) provides a strong, reliable score, we remain cautious about the overall team efficiency should any of our \"Pending\" lineup assumptions shift dramatically before first pitch. We are currently comfortable with the risk profile of these starters, prioritizing the speed-oriented ceiling provided by **Hyeseong Kim** and the power-platoon splits provided by **Colt Keith** and **Trea Turner**.",
